SIMPLE: dissolute
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dissolute
<hw>Dis"so*lute</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>dissolutus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>dissolvere</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>dissolu</ets>. See <er>Dissolve</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>With
nerves unstrung; weak.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Loosed from restraint; recklessly abandoned to
sensual pleasures; esp., loose in morals and conduct; profligate;
wanton; lewd; debauched.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A wild and <xex>dissolute</xex>
soldier.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Motley.</au></rj></p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <def>Engaging in excessive
drinking, or promiscuous sexual activity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Uncurbed; unbridled; disorderly; unrestrained;
reckless; wild; wanton; vicious; lax; licentious; lewd; rakish;
debauched; profligate.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dissolutely</ent>⟦br⟧
